Herring are a type of fish that can be obtained by cooking a raw herring on a fire or cooking range, requiring level 5 Cooking and granting 50 experience when successful. Players may burn a herring while cooking one, resulting in a burnt herring; the burn rate while cooking these will decrease as players reach higher Cooking levels. It will stop burning entirely at Cooking level 41 on both ranges and fires.

They can be eaten to heal 5 hitpoints.

Trivia[edit | edit source]

  • One of RuneScape's Monty Python references is revealed if players use a herring (cooked or raw) with any tree in RuneScape (except the one outside the Draynor Village bank, in which the security guard is hiding). The chatbox will state This is not the mightiest tree in the forest, in reference to one of the lines in Monty Python and the Holy Grail.
    • If used with a redwood tree that has fully grown in the Farming Guild, the chatbox will state This is not the mightiest tree in the forest; it is fairly mighty though.
    • If used with the Grand Tree, the chatbox will state It can't be done! in reference to another line in the movie.
    • If used with the blisterwood tree, the chatbox will state This is indeed a mighty tree. But alas, it is not the mightiest tree in the forest.
    • The Christmas Tree has no herring messages.
      • During the 2020 Christmas event, the message was indeterminable. The chatbox may state: I can't reach that! or have no message at all where the player may step towards the tree and step back again.
      • During the 2021 Christmas event, the chatbox states: Nothing interesting happens.
    • The evergreen tree from the 2021 Halloween event is an exception: It doesn't have a herring message.
